The majority of the items suggest that Angelista is a priest." },
  ["anna"] = { 2, "daughter of Fredrik Farley", "Anna is the daughter of Fredrik Farley and Verina. She is older than King Anduin Wrynn." },
  ["antonidas (alternate universe)"] = { 2, "", "In the alternate timeline where Thrall died as an infant, Antonidas was still ruling Dalaran and its Kirin Tor during the reign of the King Aedelas Blackmoore after the Battle of Blackrock Spire. Antonidas and the Kirin Tor severed all ties with K..." },
  ["antonius"] = { 2, "", "Antonius was one of the One Hundred magi of Arathor. He, Decindra, and their apprentices chose to accompany Thoradin on his quest to find the origins of humanity, which ended in disaster when they broke the seals on the Tomb of Tyr and were killed..." },
  ["anyndra"] = { 2, "night elven member of the Watchers", "Anyndra was a night elven member of the Watchers and Maiev Shadowsong's second-in-command. She accompanied her to Outland to hunt Illidan Stormrage and Sarius was in love with her." },
  ["aodhan falamar"] = { 2, "young human mage", "Aodhan Falamar is a young human mage and a student under Master Simeon. At the start of the Nexus War, Dalaran was attacked by blue dragons and Aodhan was tricked into freeing his uncle from the Violet Hold." },
  ["apari"] = { 2, "Zandalari witch", "Apari is a Zandalari witch and the leader of the Widow's Bite, a faction of Zandalari rebels who oppose the rule of Queen Talanji. She had white hair, walked with a noticeable limp, and was always accompanied by her lieutenant and bodyguard Tayo a..." },
  ["apothecary eli"] = { 2, "member of the Royal Apothecary Society", "Apothecary Eli was a member of the Royal Apothecary Society. She was killed by Citizen Wilkes." },
  ["apprentice argoly"] = { 2, "apprentice under Ansirem Runeweaver", "Apprentice Argoly was an apprentice under Ansirem Runeweaver. After being swiftly trained by Archmage Ataeric, he was sent to Runeweaver as an apprentice." },
  ["aradria cloudflyer"] = { 2, "night elven expert hippogryph rider", "Aradria Cloudflyer was a night elven expert hippogryph rider, one of the best in Ashenvale. She was tasked by Commander Haldrissa Woodshaper to send a missive to Darnassus and inform Tyrande Whisperwind that the Horde have infiltrated Ashenvale." },
  ["aramil"] = { 2, "former guard at Stormwind Keep", "Aramil was a former guard at Stormwind Keep who now served as Turalyon's assistant in all things nonmilitary. He was mentioned when Gelbin Mekkatorque asked Turalyon for aid against a rat infestation in the Deeprun Tram." },
  ["ararat"] = { 2, "warrior", "Ararat was a warrior. His blood was infused with glimmering steel, spilled by dragons, gods, and demons." },
  ["aratas"] = { 2, "ruler of the perfect ones", "High Khan Aratas was the ruler of the perfect ones, a race of centaur created by a powerful earth elemental after the Cataclysm. He united all of the centaur tribes of Kalimdor into a massive army, with the goal of destroying the \"mongrel\" races o..." },
  ["aratas' father"] = { 2, "huge", "The unnamed father of Aratas was a huge and powerful earth elemental who appeared in Maraudon after the Cataclysm. He created a new race of centaur known as the perfect ones, led by Aratas, with the intent of conquering Azeroth and purging it of i..." },
  ["archetus the mad designer"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of Archetus the Mad Designer is found in Revendreth in the Endmire between the Edge of Sin and Death's End." },
  ["arden"] = { 2, "captain of the guard of Mardenholde Keep", "Arden was the captain of the guard of Mardenholde Keep and one of the closest friends of governor Tirion Fordring of the principality of Hearthglen. However, prior to the Third War, when Tirion fell from grace as a result of trying to save the orc..." },
  ["ardogan"] = { 2, "Arathorian mage", "Ardogan was an Arathorian mage and an early ruler of the city of Dalaran." },
  ["ardwynn"] = { 2, "human", "Ardwynn is a human who guarded the Dark Portal in the Hellfire Peninsula when the forces of Azeroth first emerged on Outland. He and his companions blocked the path for Jorad Mace, citing that he was proclaimed deserter." },
  ["aredhel"] = { 2, "wife of Karlain", "Aredhel was the wife of Karlain who was accidentally killed by her husband when a man seeking to be Karlain's apprentice attempted to rape her. An image of her appeared before Karlain in Karazhan years later due to the tower's mysterious ability t..." },
  ["arellas fireleaf"] = { 2, "", "Arellas Fireleaf has a large statue erected in his honor in the Hall of Champions, located in the Scarlet Monastery in the Tirisfal Glades.  A citizen of Quel'Thalas, Fireleaf became the High Wizard of the Scarlet Crusade." },
  ["argaleus"] = { 2, "powerful mage", "Argaleus was a powerful mage. He created a book containing magically enchanted symbols, which, upon touch would activate powerful spells." },
  ["arietta"] = { 2, "daughter of Elyrion Fogsong", "Arietta was the daughter of Elyrion Fogsong and Ellaene. She was determined to become a Sentinel alongside her mother, but the two of them were killed in a battle." },
  ["arif"] = { 2, "human", "Arif was a human that followed Maddox to Andorhal looking for the defeat of the Scourge. During the battle he lighted a house and discovered it was full of undead ghouls." },
  ["arko"] = { 2, "inexperienced mage", "Arko is an inexperienced mage that was assigned to Ziya's plundersquad, which was tasked to raid Pandaren treasuries, temples, and armories for valuables and weapons to fuel the Horde war machine.
Spending the night on the chilly northern shore of..." },
  ["arkus"] = { 2, "ogre of the Dire Maul Gordunni clan", "Arkus was an ogre of the Dire Maul Gordunni clan. He guarded Dire Maul and was sent by King Gordok to the gate when the Hidden attacked." },
  ["arnaera"] = { 2, "night elf buried at Tel'anor in Suramar", "Arnaera is a night elf buried at Tel'anor in Suramar." },
  ["arrexis"] = { 2, "powerful", "Arrexis was a powerful and well known archmage of the Violet Citadel before the First War. He was also secretly a member of the Council of Tirisfal and wielded  [Ebonchill], the staff of Alodi, the first Guardian." },
  ["arrowflight"] = { 2, "white quel'dorei mare steed", "Arrowflight was a white quel'dorei mare steed and the mount of Lireesa Windrunner before the Great Wars, gifted by King Anasterian.
At the onset of the Second War, Verath and Lireesa were sent to Lordaeron City, so they set out on their horses." },
  ["arva"] = { 2, "one-eyed", "Arva was a one-eyed, four-toothed goblin first mate of Flynn Fairwind. She was allegedly killed in a tragic harpooning accident." },
  ["arvell"] = { 2, "night elf druid", "Arvell was a night elf druid and the best friend of Ralaar Fangfire. He fought alongside Malfurion Stormrage and the rest of the druids, during the War of the Satyr." },
  ["arwis blackstone"] = { 2, "dwarf", "Arwis Blackstone is a dwarf that was part of an Alliance expedition sent to Silithus to study Azerite and survey the Horde forces alongside Sentinel Cordressa Briarbow, Sapphronetta Flivvers, Gavvin Stoutarm and Inge Ironfist. After the Horde atta..." },
  ["asgrim the dreadkiller"] = { 2, "vrykul", "Asgrim the Dreadkiller was a vrykul whose hatred for the kvaldir was unmatched. He made it his life's work to slay as many of Helya's minions as possible, and his deeds were so great that Helya sent the Naglfar for him." },
  ["ashigos"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Ashigos was a blue dragon who was slain by the black dragonflight. His name is on a Fresh Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["aszune"] = { 2, "night elf princess", "Aszune was a night elf princess who, long ago, mocked the Oracle's wisdom. As punishment, she was transformed into living stone." },
  ["atai'natha"] = { 2, "leader of the Amani forest trolls", "Atai'natha was a leader of the Amani forest trolls who used a powerful magical claw to enforce his rule. The  [Lost Codex of the Amani] spends a particularly long time describing him." },
  ["atropa"] = { 2, "", "Atropa was stationed aboard the Elwynn which was stationed off of the coast Tanaris due to the Horde presence in the area." },
  ["atulhet"] = { 2, "tol'vir buried within the Tombs of the Precursors in Uldum", "Atulhet was a tol'vir buried within the Tombs of the Precursors in Uldum. He was a prophet who held off a troves of enemies by channeling the power of the sun." },
  ["atyrannus"] = { 2, "green drake", "Atyrannus is a green drake and one of Lailastrasza's closest companions. Atyrannus' egg was among the primal dragon eggs that were stolen from their nests by the titan-forged under the orders of the dragonflights." },
  ["avinal"] = { 2, "weathered human captain of a convoy ship affiliated to th...", "Avinal was the weathered human captain of a convoy ship affiliated to the Theramore military. Usually stationed at Northwatch Hold, he regularly patrolled the waters between there and Ratchet." },
  ["ayala the relentless"] = { 2, "warrior", "Ayala the Relentless is a warrior who cut down foe after foe in the pits of Valhalas on his way to legend. Becoming more lethal as his opponents weakened, he was truly terrifying to spectate." },
  ["aymestrasz"] = { 2, "red drake", "Aymestrasz is a red drake and one of Lailastrasza's companions, whom she considers to be her second-in-command. The duo and their friends fought against the djaradin, and he helped her to lead a devastating assault against Scalecracker Keep." },
  ["azal the fangnifiscent"] = { 2, "nerubian depicted by a statue in the Skeins in the City o...", "Azal the Fangnifiscent is a nerubian depicted by a statue in the Skeins in the City of Threads, on the northwestern side of the Royal Preservatorium. The statue's plaque can only be understood while under the effects of  [Potion of Polymorphic Tra..." },
  ["azarian"] = { 2, "member of the black dragonflight", "Azarian was a member of the black dragonflight who defected to the Primalist cause, an act for which Azarian was brought to the dungeons of the Obsidian Citadel for questioning." },
  ["azeroth (titan)"] = { 2, "nascent titan worldsoul", "Azeroth, called Aln'hara by the haranir, is a nascent titan worldsoul, growing within the core of the eponymous planet. Keeper Archaedas described her as being a possible candidate for the \"Prime Worldsoul\"." },
  ["azgoth"] = { 2, "annihilan", "The Doom Lord Azgoth was an annihilan who dwelled in a citadel on a Burning Legion-controlled world, inhabited by felguards and felbats.
At some point, Margrave Akarek and Baroness Draka of the House of Eyes traveled to Azgoth's planet and stole a..." },
  ["azj'aqir (tol'vir)"] = { 2, "tol'vir sorcerer", "Azj'Aqir was a tol'vir sorcerer. He was said to possess a scepter that would allow him to control a Qiraji battle tank outside of its Silithus home." },
  ["azora"] = { 2, "unknown entity", "Azora is an unknown entity. Evidence of Azora is uncommon." },
  ["azzinoth"] = { 2, "powerful doomguard commander of the Burning Legion slain ...", "Azzinoth was a powerful doomguard commander of the Burning Legion slain by Illidan Stormrage during the War of the Ancients, 10,000 years ago. He was the original wielder of Illidan's warglaives, which the demon hunter claimed after slaying his foe." },
  ["ba'rak"] = { 2, "", "Ba'rak was one of the few orcs that survived the Alliance assault on Hellfire Citadel. He followed Kargath Bladefist to Nagrand to gather some warriors for the Horde." },
  ["ba'sim"] = { 2, "broker belonging to Cartel Ba", "Ba'sim is a broker belonging to Cartel Ba. He works at the P.O.S.T. in Tazavesh and is a friend of Al'dalil." },
  ["baenan"] = { 2, "dwarf paladin", "Baenan is a dwarf paladin who was stationed aboard the Elwynn which was stationed off of the coast Tanaris due to the Horde presence in the area." },
  ["balacgos"] = { 2, "elder offspring of the great Aspect Malygos", "Balacgos was an elder offspring of the great Aspect Malygos. He was especially gifted even among dragons who wielded the powers of the arcane with natural ease." },
  ["balambor"] = { 2, "elf", "Balambor was an elf that was training to become a demon hunter. While he survived the first part of the ritual, he was driven mad, attacked his fellow trainees and died while fighting them." },
  ["balcephoth"] = { 2, "unknown being", "Balcephoth of the felshadows is an unknown being who telepathically communicated with Vitus Darkwalker, a Gilnean warlock, and taught him the forbidden secrets of corruption. He is presumably a demon." },
  ["banagos"] = { 2, "blue dragon using human visage", "Banagos is a blue dragon using human visage. He was sent with Kirygosa to discover what had happened to the blue dragons sent to move the Focusing Iris to a secure location." },
  ["bang"] = { 2, "personal bruiser of Klaxz Boompowder", "Bang was the personal bruiser of Klaxz Boompowder, a trade prince of the Steamwheedle Cartel. Like Klaxz's wife Slixi, Bang noticed and was unsettled by the strange behavior his boss displayed after he fell victim to the Uninvited Guest, which cau..." },
  ["barnabas"] = { 2, "brother of Burrian Coalpart", "Barnabas was the brother of Burrian Coalpart. Legend has it that he was eaten by Margol the Rager." },
  ["barnes (cycle of hatred)"] = { 2, "human killed by an orc", "Corporal Barnes was a human killed by an orc. Davin saw his body falling to water." },
  ["bartholemew"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Bartholemew was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["bathet"] = { 2, "", "Bathet was among a number of the Neferset who joined the vast majority of his people in siding with Deathwing in order to reverse the curse of flesh. Though after learning about Bathet from Menrim, Li Li Stormstout theorizes that Bathet was less f..." },
  ["battlemaster bröng"] = { 2, "leader of the Garad'kra", "Battlemaster Bröng is the leader of the Garad'kra, a group of elite Horde militias. Just after the militia's founding following the Cataclysm, Bröng assembled the Garad'kra in Orgrimmar's Ring of Valor to give them their first orders: ending the n..." },
  ["baxtan"] = { 2, "great goblin mage", "Baxtan is a great goblin mage. He is the author of  [Baxtan: On Destructive Magics]." },
  ["beast of lyquokk strait"] = { 2, "", "A large, unnamed sea monster inhabited Lyquokk Strait on the western coast of the Howling Fjord until it was killed by the tuskarr Taruka, who subsequently became known as \"Beastkiller\"." },
  ["beathan"] = { 2, "Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War", "Beathan was a Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War. He was the one who reported Kurdran that Moray and Seaghdh died and Alpin and Lachtin were knocked from their gryphons because of the forest trolls helping the orcs." },
  ["bek"] = { 2, "Theramore soldier under Colonel Lorena", "Major Bek was a Theramore soldier under Colonel Lorena. When Lorena received an order from Kristoff to lead Northwatch Hold's forces, Bek was amongst those whom Lorena chose as her senior staff." },
  ["bellthazor"] = { 2, "human rogue", "Bellthazor of Darkshire is a human rogue. After buying Miles Corebender a couple of drinks in a Gadgetzan inn, Miles revealed to Bellthazor his and Kova’s quest for the reclusive orc seer Dhambeela." },
  ["benge"] = { 2, "young orc killed by the hydra Trigore the Lasher in the W...", "Benge was a young orc killed by the hydra Trigore the Lasher in the Wailing Caverns during his om'gora. His body, torn and cold, was found by a party of warriors and brought to Orgrimmar, where his father turned away from his corpse out of grief." },
  ["beregos"] = { 2, "member of the blue dragonflight", "Beregos was a member of the blue dragonflight who served as the archlibrarian of the Azure Archives.
Beregos worked with Sindragosa to create an army of illusions to make the borders of the Broodlands appear far more defended than they were, and l..." },
  ["berian"] = { 2, "member of the black dragonflight", "Berian was a member of the black dragonflight and one of the swiftest fliers available to them. He was sent to Umbrenion with a fulgurite produced by Raszageth during her attack upon a mortal village." },
  ["bernard"] = { 2, "most famous of all Alterac brewhounds", "Bernard is the most famous of all Alterac brewhounds. He is credited with saving upwards of 50 lives — many of them dwarf and orc soldiers dragged out of the snow beneath the treacherous bridges of Alterac Valley." },
  ["bertha"] = { 2, "fisherman by the lake", "Bertha was a human located at Tarren Mill in Old Hillsbrad Foothills. Her husband is a fisherman by the lake." },
  ["beth'amara"] = { 2, "", "Beth'Amara was one of the Highborne's most influential alchemists. The wizard alone was said to have mastered transmuting metals among other things." },
  ["bezime"] = { 2, "Zandalari troll noble", "Bezime was a Zandalari troll noble whose family was among those punished for their ties to the traitor Yazma, though the Zanchuli Council found the family cleared of any wrongdoing. When his daughter, Nav'rae, petitioned aid from the crown in bein..." },
  ["bezok"] = { 2, "brick maker", "Bezok was a brick maker who lived on Copper Street in Bilgewater Port and he watched Jastor Gallywix trick Skezzo and his gang. Soon after the battle, Jastor made a deal with Bezok to give him his business in return for yearly compensation." },
  ["billy (boralus)"] = { 2, "", "Billy is one of the orphans living at the orphanage in Boralus. He is best friends with Liam." },
  ["bishop (rise of the lich king)"] = { 2, "only person besides the royal family", "A bishop from the Church of the Holy Light was responsible for holding services and providing blessings for the Menethil family in their private chapel in Capital City. He was apparently highly trusted, as he was the only person besides the royal ..." },
  ["bjarl"] = { 2, "", "Bjarl was one of the dwarves under Rom's command. At one moment Rom commanded him to secure a safe brook." },
  ["blackhand"] = { 2, "chieftain of the mighty Blackrock clan", "Blackhand was the chieftain of the mighty Blackrock clan and the first Warchief of the Old Horde until he was killed by Orgrim Doomhammer near the end of the First War. He was known throughout Draenor and Azeroth alike as a brutal tyrant." },
  ["blackklaw"] = { 2, "ebon gryphon mount of Daerion of the Stormwind Assassin's...", "Blackklaw was the ebon gryphon mount of Daerion of the Stormwind Assassin's Guild, who tried to kill Lo'Gosh. Blackklaw was killed by Valeera Sanguinar." },
  ["blacknails"] = { 2, "member of the Defias Brotherhood mentioned in  [A Mysteri...", "Blacknails, a member of the Defias Brotherhood mentioned in  [A Mysterious Message], is probably the person in charge of Jangolode Mine or Gold Coast Quarry (or both), since the Defias Messenger, the carrier of the letter, is walking between the D..." },
  ["blokk"] = { 2, "simpleminded ogre", "Blokk is a simpleminded ogre who served as the mount of the goblin alchemist Rumblefitz and was hired by Zhahara Darksquall to find the Pearl of Pandaria." },
  ["blondy"] = { 2, "rare blonde orc", "Blondy was a rare blonde orc that participated in the First War." },
  ["bloodhorn"] = { 2, "tauren vendor located in Flayers' Point of Desolace", "Bloodhorn is a tauren vendor located in Flayers' Point of Desolace. She is an acquaintance of the captain of the Wavestrider, Greydon Thorne." },
  ["blossom"] = { 2, "ram", "Blossom is a ram that was briefly befriended and named by Taryndrella south of Cliffwalker Post in the Stonetalon Mountains. Taryndralla asked him to get her and Aramar Thorne to Northwatch Expedition Base Camp." },
  ["bluebell"] = { 2, "human stationed in Westguard Keep in Howling Fjord", "Bluebell is a human stationed in Westguard Keep in Howling Fjord. She has blue eyes." },
  ["blythe (stromgarde)"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Blythe was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["bob bigheart"] = { 2, "dwarf character in Smokywood Pastures Presents: A Winter ...", "Bob Bigheart is a dwarf character in Smokywood Pastures Presents: A Winter Veil Carol. He is a scribe working at Scrounge's counting house." },
  ["bojsanz"] = { 2, "leader of the Heart's Guard during the War of the Scaleborn", "Bojsanz was the leader of the Heart's Guard during the War of the Scaleborn and a favored champion of Alexstrasza.
Bojsanz slew Vyranoth's lieutenant Vitelenoth at Icewing Rift with the help of Stoltria, and alongside Levarian engaged in combat wi..." },
  ["bolgar"] = { 2, "follower of the Twilight's Hammer", "Bolgar was a follower of the Twilight's Hammer who had purchased a copy of the book The Powers Below from Gerrig Bonegrip of Bonegrip's Runes and Dooms in Ironforge. He seems to have studied the book thoroughly in the year he owned it, writing not..." },
  ["bolik"] = { 2, "Captain of the Horde trading ship Orgath'ar", "Bolik was the Captain of the Horde trading ship Orgath'ar. A young orc, born in the human internment camp system, he felt that it was important to look as little like the slaves of old as possible, and groomed himself in a way very unusual for the..." },
  ["bolts"] = { 2, "pet mechanical squirrel of Fala Fizzlesprocket in the Smo...", "Bolts is the pet mechanical squirrel of Fala Fizzlesprocket in the Smokywood Storytime episode \"A Very Smokywood Winter Veil\". Fala's father Fritz made the squirrel for her as a birthday present." },
  ["bongbong"] = { 2, "parrot of the goblin Krazzet", "Bongbong is a parrot of the goblin Krazzet, who won him in a bet against Flynn Fairwind." },
  ["booraven"] = { 2, "Theramore soldier under Colonel Lorena", "Corporal Booraven was a Theramore soldier under Colonel Lorena. She was the rare case of a magic-sensitive human that could sniff out fel or arcane magic where the naked human eye couldn't." },
  ["bor"] = { 2, "mysterious entity mentioned throughout Northrend", "Bor is a mysterious entity mentioned throughout Northrend, mainly in the Storm Peaks near Frostborn territories and by the kvaldir." },
  ["bordok"] = { 2, "ogre of the Gordunni clan", "Bordok was an ogre of the Gordunni clan and a part of Wordok's group. He was killed by Makasa Flintwill in Feralas." },
  ["botaan"] = { 2, "last of the three final Sporemounds faced by Grond", "Botaan was the last of the three final Sporemounds faced by Grond, the other two being Naanu and Zang. It was covered with primal forestlands." },
  ["bradok"] = { 2, "", "Bradok was one of the first dragon riders of the Dragonmaw clan during the Second War. He noticed Gul'dan's fleet sailing for the Tomb of Sargeras, and went to discover why he had abandoned his post at Quel'Thalas and set out onto the Great Sea." },
  ["bradshaw"] = { 2, "old Gilnean human", "Bradshaw is an old Gilnean human who during the worgen attack on the kingdom was writing a journal about the events transpiring in Stormglen Village. While the rest of the town left for Tempest's Reach, Bradshaw stayed." },
  ["brakor"] = { 2, "legendary orc hero of the Thunderlord clan in ancient times", "Brakor was a legendary orc hero of the Thunderlord clan in ancient times, when they were still enslaved by the ogres of Frostfire. He wielded the legendary spear  [Gronnsbane], which was blessed by the elements and beasts of the land, but which lo..." },
  ["briggs"] = { 2, "member of the Argent Dawn", "Briggs was a member of the Argent Dawn. He was killed by another member of his order who had been raised from undeath by the Scourge." },
  ["brightmane"] = { 2, "", "Brightmane was one of the white horses kept by the Balnir family at their farmstead in the Tirisfal Glades. In the winter of 4 ADP, she gave birth to a colt, Invincible, with some assistance from Jorum Balnir, Jarim Balnir, and the visiting Prince..." },
  ["brigligos"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Brigligos was a blue dragon who was killed in a magical accident. His name is on a Fresh Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["briln"] = { 2, "orc captain of the Blood", "Briln was the orc captain of the Blood and Thunder. He lost his eye in the battle against Alliance forces commanded by Admiral Proudmoore." },
  ["bristlefur"] = { 2, "wyvern mount of Valeera Sanguinar", "Bristlefur is the wyvern mount of Valeera Sanguinar. Valeera stole him from Tarm, when fleeing from her new gladiator master, Helka Grimtotem." },
  ["bristlemaw"] = { 2, "quilboar", "Bristlemaw is a quilboar." },
  ["brlee"] = { 2, "member of the Gordunni Gladiator Team of Ancient Draenor:...", "Brlee was a member of the Gordunni Gladiator Team of Ancient Draenor: the previous year's team champions of the Crimson Ring tournament. During his gladiator fight in Dire Maul against Varian \"Lo'Gosh\" Wrynn, Valeera Sanguinar and Broll Bearmantle..." },
  ["brodog"] = { 2, "orc", "Brodog was an orc who lived on Draenor during the time of the Second War." },
  ["brogan falamar"] = { 2, "father of Aodhan", "Brogan Falamar was the father of Aodhan and Kedehern. He was very proud of Kedehern's choice of becoming a paladin, but he became rather disappointed when Aodhan chose to become a mage." },
  ["brogas"] = { 2, "young orc warrior in the Dragonmaw clan under the command...", "Brogas was a young orc warrior in the Dragonmaw clan under the command of Nekros at Grim Batol. He was the chief handler of dragons." },
  ["bron (mage)"] = { 2, "young human mage", "Bron is a young human mage, and, alongside Aodhan, a student under Master Simeon." },
  ["brother adam"] = { 2, "", "Brother Adam and Brother David were brilliant mathematicians and monks, always blabbing about abacuses and parabolas." },
  ["brother cuo"] = { 2, "general of the Thunder King", "Brother Cuo was one of the Shado-Pan agents chosen to aid Vol'jin and his companions in their attempt to thwart the resurrection of Warlord Kao, a general of the Thunder King. However, the group ended up being captured by the Zandalari and Cuo was..." },
  ["brother dao"] = { 2, "general of the Thunder King", "Brother Dao was one of the Shado-Pan agents chosen to aid Vol'jin and his companions in their attempt to thwart the resurrection of Warlord Kao, a general of the Thunder King. However the group ended up being captured by the Zandalari and Dao foun..." },
  ["brother david"] = { 2, "", "Brother David and Brother Adam were brilliant mathematicians and monks, always blabbing about abacuses and parabolas." },
  ["bryndaor"] = { 2, "unknown being", "Bryndaor is an unknown being, presumably vrykul, who guards the gates of Helheim for all eternity as a punishment. His  [Shackles of Bryndaor] can be looted." },
  ["brynild the brewmaster"] = { 2, "", "Brynild the Brewmaster knew the two monks named Brother Adam and Brother David." },
  ["brynjar"] = { 2, "vrykul", "Old Brynjar is a vrykul who recorded a chapter in The Legend of Odyn, \"Great Odyn and the Firelord\", about Odyn and Tyr battling Ragnaros the Firelord." },
  ["bungledorf"] = { 2, "main character in the children's story The Worst Mage in ...", "Bungledorf is the main character in the children's story The Worst Mage in Dalaran: A Children's Book. His story is about a mage who didn't think he was cut out for the class." },
  ["burx"] = { 2, "chief warrior in the Horde", "Burx was a chief warrior in the Horde and Thrall's closest advisor in the years after the Battle for Mount Hyjal. Burx was also secretly a member of the Burning Blade cult, not out of disrespect for his Warchief but rather out of an intense hatred..." },
  ["buwei"] = { 2, "pandaren refugee", "Buwei was a pandaren refugee who entered the Vale of Eternal Blossoms after the gate to it was opened. He was soon joined with Li Li Stormstout." },
  ["byakko"] = { 2, "animal companion of Wotan", "Byakko was the animal companion of Wotan, the Master Hunter of the Winterskorn." },
  ["byrok"] = { 2, "orcish warrior", "Byrok was an orcish warrior. A veteran of the First and Second Wars, he spent years enslaved in the humans' internment camps before being freed by Thrall." },
  ["cackle"] = { 2, "gnoll matriarch of the Grimtail clan living in the Last F...", "Cackle is the gnoll matriarch of the Grimtail clan living in the Last Forest of Desolace. She traded with Wavestrider's Captain, Greydon Thorne." },
  ["calcia"] = { 2, "", "Calcia was one of Neltharion's most trusted scale-crafters and the leader of the black dragonflight's scalesmiths.
She and her scalesmiths worked with the blue dragonflight to stabilize the earth beneath the Broodlands during Iridikron's onslaught..." },
  ["captain (crawler)"] = { 2, "huge pet crawler of the goblin hunter Chikkers", "The Captain is the huge pet crawler of the goblin hunter Chikkers. She stands nearly as tall as Lorash Sunbeam's waist and has a light blue shell that is almost as big as her goblin master and probably weighs twice as much." },
  ["captain cuergo"] = { 2, "pirate known for plundering", "Captain Cuergo is a pirate known for plundering and hanging around Lost Rigger Cove.
Although he is supposedly the leader of the Southsea Freebooters in Lost Rigger Cove, he never makes an appearance and is only mentioned in questlines." },
  ["caruk bloodwind"] = { 2, "Highmountain tauren", "Caruk Bloodwind is a Highmountain tauren that was the first leatherworker in Highmountain. He invented tanning." },
  ["castillian"] = { 2, "mysterious mage of the Argent Dawn", "Castillian was a mysterious mage of the Argent Dawn. He never spoke, wore a mask to conceal his identity, and was among those who chose to accompany Darion Mograine into Naxxramas to rescue his father, Alexandros Mograine." },
  ["cedrick fallrook"] = { 2, "ambitious", "Cedrick Fallrook was an ambitious and arrogant son of Terrence Fallrook who lived in the Fallrook Estate. His family owned a winery." },
  ["cellyn"] = { 2, "female high elf mentioned in Death Knight", "Cellyn is a female high elf mentioned in Death Knight. According to Faltora, she is a show off and she was going to organize a banquet." },
  ["celosel nightgiver"] = { 2, "void elf captain", "Celosel Nightgiver is a void elf captain who worked under Alleria Windrunner and Turalyon in their mission to hunt down and capture Sylvanas Windrunner in the Arathi Highlands. He worked closely with Senn and after discovering where Visrynn (a dar..." },
  ["chae-nan"] = { 2, "", "Chae-nan is one of Warlord Kao's bodyguards and as such was present when his master resurrected by the Zandalari trolls. Under his master's command, Chae-nan joined with the force of 500 Zandalari warriors ordered to destroy the Shado-Pan and thei..." },
  ["chalyx"] = { 2, "beloved cat pet of Emperor Ninjter", "Chalyx was the beloved cat pet of Emperor Ninjter. A clay statue was commissioned in his memory." },
  ["chamley"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Chamley was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["chantu"] = { 2, "draenei", "Chantu was a draenei whom Jaruk Bloodfyre and Leena visited at their one year anniversary. He wanted them to stay with him, but Jaruk refused, telling him that they must be on a move from his brother - J'argg Bloodfyre." },
  ["charnas"] = { 2, "goblin", "Charnas of Gadgetzan is a goblin who traveled across Azeroth and sketched its various birds. One of his books ended up with Captain Greydon Thorne and was later found by his son, Aramar Thorne." },
  ["chiang sisters"] = { 2, "", "The Chiang Sisters are two elderly pandaren women who live in Binan Village. They claim to be old enough to remember when Liu Lang had first departed from Pandaria, however Chen Stormstout doubts this, and have developed opinions of those who \"cha..." },
  ["chikkers"] = { 2, "goblin hunter", "Chikkers is a goblin hunter who participated in the Horde's invasion of Ashenvale during the War of the Thorns. His pet is a crawler named the Captain." },
  ["chinwa"] = { 2, "son of a fisherman", "Chinwa is the son of a fisherman and as a youth would compete for Yalia Sagewhisper with his friend Yenki. However Yalia possessing wisdom beyond her young years realized that their competition would not end, even after her hand had been." },
  ["choraldormi"] = { 2, "bronze dragon referenced on an Ancient Stone titled A Tim...", "Choraldormi is a bronze dragon referenced on an Ancient Stone titled A Timely Message." },
  ["christoff"] = { 2, "paladin of the Silver Hand under Duncan Senturus's command", "Christoff was a paladin of the Silver Hand under Duncan Senturus's command." },
  ["christoph"] = { 2, "human from Lordaeron", "Christoph was a human from Lordaeron who fought during the Third War. His last battle was in Andorhal alongside the Knights of the Silver Hand when Arthas invaded for the Urn of King Terenas." },
  ["chromatus"] = { 2, "first", "Chromatus is the first and only successfully formed chromatic dragon. Chromatus' five heads grant him the power of all five dragonflights." },
  ["chronicler eko"] = { 2, "ankoan of the Waveblade clan", "Chronicler Eko was an ankoan of the Waveblade clan. Eko recorded the deeds of their greatest heroes and earned her rightful place among them as well." },
  ["ciarin"] = { 2, "dwarf", "Ciarin was a dwarf that was contracted by Maddox." },
  ["cinderfoot"] = { 2, "striped moonsaber belonging to Iyneath", "Cinderfoot is a striped moonsaber belonging to Iyneath. It carried the injured Makasa Flintwill to Thal'darah Overlook." },
  ["citizen bonoan"] = { 2, "citizen of Hillsbrad Fields", "Citizen Bonoan was a citizen of Hillsbrad Fields. It is unknown what became of him after the Forsaken took over." },
  ["clai"] = { 2, "soldier under Lorena", "Clai is a soldier under Lorena. He accompanied Lorena and her army out of Northwatch." },
  ["claw (gnoll)"] = { 2, "Woodpaw gnoll brute", "Claw was the Woodpaw gnoll brute. He was a close friend to Gnaw." },
  ["clemens"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Clemens was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["cloudhoof"] = { 2, "", "Cloudhoof was one of the twin sons of Sunwalker Dezco and Leza Dawnchaser. He and his brother, Redhorn, were born in the Krasarang Wilds, their mother dying in childbirth." },
  ["cog burnwick"] = { 2, "gnomish deckhand on the Wavestrider", "Cog Burnwick was a gnomish deckhand on the Wavestrider. He died defending the ship when Captain Malus and his Hidden attacked it." },
  ["commander borton"] = { 2, "", "Commander Borton was part of the forces defending Stormwind City during the First War. King Llane commanded him as the city was under attack by orcs." },
  ["cook (character)"] = { 2, "tower's cook", "The servant Cook was one of Medivh's two servants at Karazhan — the other servant being Moroes. As her name/title implies, she was the tower's cook." },
  ["cooktholomew"] = { 2, "chef from Booty Bay", "Rufinwag nicknamed Cooktholomew is a chef from Booty Bay. He had been traveling with Bonenose and a pair of Booty Bay Buccaneers, but got lost at sea." },
  ["cora (draenei)"] = { 2, "draenei child", "Cora was a draenei child and friend of Akama who lived in the Temple of Karabor. During the temple's fall to the Horde, Akama led Cora and other civilians to safety but was unable to save the girl's mother, who was cut down by the orcs." },
  ["corewind"] = { 2, "tauren located in Freewind Post in Thousand Needles", "Corewind is a tauren located in Freewind Post in Thousand Needles. Some time after the Cataclysm, during one of the harpy attacks, he was swooped by one, but Thalia Amberhide threw a spear at the abductor, piercing her wing." },
  ["cormery"] = { 2, "guard in service of House Proudmoore", "Cormery is a guard in service of House Proudmoore. When Flynn Fairwind arrived in the city to inform Katherine and Jaina Proudmoore that Mathias Shaw had been captured by the Zandalari Empire, Cormery was one of his escorts." },
  ["coros"] = { 2, "proto-dragon of blue-green coloration", "Coros was a proto-dragon of blue-green coloration and an old rival of the blue-white Malygos. They had competed in the past over kills, territory, and strength." },
  ["corrigan"] = { 2, "dwarf", "Corrigan was a dwarf who, according to a song written about him, defeated a dragon." },
  ["cortello"] = { 2, "unknown person", "Cortello is an unknown person who was responsible for the cortello's riddle treasure hunt." },
  ["cotley"] = { 2, "Forsaken apothecary", "Cotley is a Forsaken apothecary that had come to care for a group of Horde refugees within the Arathi Highlands.
One day, the refugees were approached Visrynn, a dark ranger, who joined them on the condition that they take a vow of silence." },
  ["count erlgadin"] = { 2, "member of the human aristocracy", "Count Erlgadin is a member of the human aristocracy. He became renowned for his generosity, while lobbying for improved working conditions for the Stonemasons' Guild during the restoration of Stormwind after the Second War." },
  ["courageous"] = { 2, "mount of Terenas Menethil II", "Courageous was the mount of Terenas Menethil II." },
  ["cousin ich"] = { 2, "pandaren on the Wandering Isle", "Cousin Ich is a pandaren on the Wandering Isle that creates fireworks." },
  ["cowry"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Cowry was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["cox"] = { 2, "large human", "Cox is a large human and the partner of the famous detective Halford Ramsey. Together, Cox and Halford were investigating the Starlight Slasher murders; however, the two of them did not get along." },
  ["craishae"] = { 2, "subject of many myths", "Craishae was a legendary lost queen of Arathor. She is the subject of many myths, of which one, The Ballad of Craishae the First Flame, tells of how she became the first person to wield a combination of fire and the Light (something similar to the..." },
  ["creedy"] = { 2, "leader of gang of bounty hunters", "Creedy was the leader of gang of bounty hunters. He was captured by Hemet Nesingwary when the bounty hunters where hunting three frostsaber cubs, that Hemet was protecting." },
  ["crevan falamar"] = { 2, "human mage", "Crevan Falamar was a human mage. He had aligned himself with Malygos during the Nexus War and was therefore placed inside the Violet Hold by the Kirin Tor." },
  ["crillian"] = { 2, "honorable headmaster", "Crillian is an honorable headmaster and master of Stalvan Mistmantle. He gave Stalvan the advice to move out of Stormwind." },
  ["cristalstrasz"] = { 2, "leader of the red dragonflight's Ruby Flamebringers durin...", "Cristalstrasz was the leader of the red dragonflight's Ruby Flamebringers during the War of the Scaleborn, and was personally responsible for the deaths of countless Primalists. Fyrakk regarded him as a brute when he saw Cristalstrasz at the Battl..." },
  ["crunchola"] = { 2, "modified shredder created by Grizzek Fizzwrench", "The Crunchola is a modified shredder created by Grizzek Fizzwrench, who also fondly referred to it as Crunchy. One of its mechanically operated limbs is outfitted with a grasping hand augmented by an energy beam, with the idea being that the energ..." },
  ["curigosa"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Curigosa was a blue dragon who was killed by Neltharion's betrayal during the War of the Ancients. Her name is on a Faded Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["cyrce"] = { 2, "leader of the Sturmvyn clan of iron vrykul", "Cyrce is the leader of the Sturmvyn clan of iron vrykul. She and her clan lived in the Storm Peaks, where she was the first vrykul to tame a galeorn, Thrayir, after all else had failed." },
  ["cysanz"] = { 2, "ancient proto-dragon", "Cysanz was an ancient proto-dragon and one of Vyranoth's supporters during the War of the Scaleborn. He had been reluctant to join the Primalist cause, but as with many of the ancient proto-dragon holdouts he was swayed when word reached him that ..." },
  ["daerion the assassin"] = { 2, "assassin hired by Katrana Prestor through Gakca to kill t...", "Daerion the Assassin was the assassin hired by Katrana Prestor through Gakca to kill the strong-willed Varian.
Daerion met with Magatha Grimtotem, who was told by the Forsaken of his arrival." },
  ["dagath"] = { 2, "", "Dagath seemed to have been a Wildhammer dwarf of some renown as Falstad Dragonreaver was known to have sworn to the phrase Dagath's Hammer." },
  ["daglir"] = { 2, "nightborne living in Suramar City", "Daglir is a nightborne living in Suramar City. He is a premier fruit vendor who won the favor of the high nobles." },
  ["dalgin"] = { 2, "leader of a caravan", "Dalgin was a leader of a caravan that was heading to Uldum and were accompanied by Li Li a Chen after Deathwing's death. The caravan stumbled upon a group of tol'vir who took them to the city of Ramkahen." },
  ["dansel adams"] = { 2, "hunter", "Dansel Adams is a hunter and a member of the Scarlet Crusade. During a routine purging of heathens in the Scourge infested Plaguewood, he witnessed Naxxramas leaving." },
  ["darckli"] = { 2, "archmage with innemurable achievements", "Darckli was an archmage with innemurable achievements, among which mastering the art of breathing dragonfire directly from his mouth." },
  ["dargo"] = { 2, "", "Dargo was one of the three Bloodsail Buccaneers that attacked the draenei priestess Iridi for gold in Ratchet." },
  ["dargonax"] = { 2, "twilight dragon created by Sintharia", "Dargonax was a twilight dragon created by Sintharia, who regarded the mighty creature as her child. He appears in the World of Warcraft novel Night of the Dragon." },
  ["dark eagle"] = { 2, "eagle with gold-and-brown feathers", "The Dark Eagle was an eagle with gold-and-brown feathers, tortured and cruelly warped by the Amani trolls and their dark magic, twisting it into a true monster. After a quiet time, the trolls launched a well-planned incursion with their finest war..." },
  ["darkfire (arakkoa)"] = { 2, "unknown entity or thing mentioned only by Sethekk arakkoa...", "Darkfire is an unknown entity or thing mentioned only by Sethekk arakkoa inside Sethekk Halls: \"Darkfire -- avenge us!\" Said along with \"Protect the Veil!\" and \"In Terokk's name!\" There is otherwise no information or context about who or what Dark..." },
  ["darkness (character)"] = { 2, "", "References to an apparent individual called Darkness are a running joke that began in various character quotations Warcraft III: Reign of Chaos and continues in Heroes of the Storm. The joke has its origins when demon hunters said \"darkness called..." },
  ["darmeto"] = { 2, "technomancer of Ma'nussa", "Darmeto was a technomancer of Ma'nussa who held membership in the Ravel." },
  ["darren boyle"] = { 2, "boy living in Lakeshire in Redridge Mountains", "Darren Boyle is a boy living in Lakeshire in Redridge Mountains. When Aramar Thorne was six and was playing by Lake Everstill, the nasty Darren pushed him down into the sand and took his horse." },
  ["dartol"] = { 2, "creator of the ever popular [Dartol's Rod of Transformation]", "Dartol was the creator of the ever popular [Dartol's Rod of Transformation]. Not much is known about Dartol, except for what Teronis has depicted in his journal." },
  ["davan"] = { 2, "briefly mentioned dwarf", "Davan was a briefly mentioned dwarf who was ordered by Falric to fire on Mal'Ganis's undead." },
  ["davin"] = { 2, "commandant of Northwatch Hold for three years by the time...", "Major Davin was the commandant of Northwatch Hold for three years by the time of the events of Cycle of Hatred." },
  ["daz"] = { 2, "dreadtick pet of Apari", "Daz was the dreadtick pet of Apari, the leader of the Widow's Bite. After Seshi was sacrificed, Daz went to eat his corpse only to be stopped by Apari, due to the fallen troll being poisoned." },
  ["decindra"] = { 2, "", "Decindra was one of the One Hundred magi of Arathor. She, Antonius, and their apprentices chose to accompany Thoradin on his quest to find the origins of humanity, which ended in disaster when they broke the seals on the Tomb of Tyr and were kille..." },
  ["defender of the crown"] = { 2, "name given to refer to the leader of the human forces of ...", "The Defender of the Crown is the name given to refer to the leader of the human forces of the Kingdom of Stormwind during the First War.
As a loyal subject of King Llane, the Defender fought on multiple battlefields against the orcs and their lead..." },
  ["deliah andrean"] = { 2, "wife of Raleigh", "Deliah Andrean, the wife of Raleigh Andrean, lived in Brill and was murdered by her friend Valdred Moray. She was buried in a mass grave near Brill, but her body was stolen by Rot Hide gnolls and taken to the Decrepit Ferry in Silverpine Forest." },
  ["deliria dawes"] = { 2, "", "Deliria Dawes is one of the undead Forsaken who remained loyal to Sylvanas Windrunner after the Fourth War and became the captain of the Banshee's Wail after the loyalists had acquired it through unknown means. Under Nathanos's command, she used t..." },
  ["denbrawn"] = { 2, "novelist of Denbrawn's Treatise on the \"Song of Aegwynn\"", "Denbrawn is the novelist of Denbrawn's Treatise on the \"Song of Aegwynn\", a book mentioned in The Last Guardian, which the mage Guzbah was reviewing at the time of his death." },
  ["denea"] = { 2, "night elf Sentinel", "Sentinel Lieutenant Denea is an night elf Sentinel and Commander Haldrissa Woodshaper's second in command. She would often question if Haldrissa was fit to lead since her age showed signs of frailty, but after her heroic actions, such as killing a..." },
  ["deng-chon"] = { 2, "father of Deng-Tai", "Deng-Chon is the father of Deng-Tai." },
  ["deng-tai"] = { 2, "", "Deng-Tai is one of Warlord Kao's bodyguards and as such was present when his master resurrected by the Zandalari trolls. Under his master's command, Deng-Tai joined with the force of 500 Zandalari warriors ordered to destroy the Shado-Pan and thei..." },
  ["dermid"] = { 2, "Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War", "Dermid was a Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War. He was the first to make contact with the humans who told him they came to fight the orcs in the Hinterlands." },
  ["desamir ferrar"] = { 2, "deckhand on the Wavestrider", "Desamir Ferrar was a deckhand on the Wavestrider. He defended the ship against the Hidden, and at some fought by the ogre Throgg." },
  ["desharin"] = { 2, "member of the green dragonflight", "Desharin (aka Desharin Greensong in guise) was a member of the green dragonflight and a loyal servant of Ysera, who took on his kaldorei guise in order to assist Thrall with his task to soothe a rampant fire elemental in Feralas. He subsequently t..." },
  ["det'rak"] = { 2, "orc", "Det'rak was an orc whose scouting party was ambushed by the Warmaul ogres. The orc perished along with Kelorr." },
  ["dethmoora darkeyes"] = { 2, "mysterious warlock", "Dethmoora Darkeyes was a mysterious warlock who met some unknown end, prompting a type of ritual implement known as a Bell of Dethmoora named after her. Mor'zul Bloodbringer was at least vaguely familiar with her, though he did not elaborate on he..." },
  ["dethorin"] = { 2, "original wielder of the Killmaim", "Dethorin was the original wielder of the Killmaim, after it appeared out of the ground in response to his cries. With it, he killed his lady Allurana and her lover for whom had been the cause of his woe and the Killmaim's appearance." },
  ["devi"] = { 2, "high elf mage from an alternate universe", "Devi is a high elf mage from an alternate universe and the apparent apprentice of Krasus, the alias of the great red dragon Korialstrasz. She is a dark-skinned elf with raven-black hair and has both a curious and inquisitive air about her that som..." },
  ["devin"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of Devin is found in Revendreth in the Crypt of the Forgotten." },
  ["dhambeela"] = { 2, "reclusive orc seer", "Dhambeela is a reclusive orc seer who sought solitude in a cave by the jungles of Un'Goro Crater. Kova was sent on a quest by Magatha Grimtotem to retrieve her." },
  ["dhink"] = { 2, "kobold taskmaster", "Dhink is a kobold taskmaster who had conducted several burglaries from the Highmountain tauren with several other kobolds. Rather than going underground, Dhink stashed the goods on top of the cave entrance to Mucksnout Den." },
  ["di chen"] = { 2, "finest fighter of his time having the ability to best any...", "Di Chen was the finest fighter of his time having the ability to best any monk who challenged him, slapping arrows out the air with ease, and even the mountains themselves were slight inconveniences for him that could be leapt over or kicked throu..." },
  ["diesalven"] = { 2, "", "The necromancer Diesalven is known to have engaged Arellas Fireleaf, High Wizard of the Scarlet Crusade, in a duel. It is not known what transpired between the two, but they were ultimately locked in eternal combat." },
  ["diodor the damned"] = { 2, "", "Formerly a decorated hero in the First War, Diodor the Damned studied necromancy and eventually became one of the first members of the Cult of the Damned.  After leading two successful assaults against the Scarlet Monastery, he was killed when the..." },
  ["distyia"] = { 2, "black dragon", "Distyia was a black dragon who the red dragon Veritistrasz loved and called a friend. After the black dragonflight succumbed to the corruption of the Old Gods, Veritistrasz recalled to adventurers listening to his story the horror he felt when he ..." },
  ["dojan firecrown"] = { 2, "emperor of the mogu", "Dojan Firecrown was an emperor of the mogu. When the saurok guards began to plunder the very people they were supposed to police Emperor Dojan responded in the traditional mogu way: the souls were ripped from every living saurok in the Vale of Ete..." },
  ["dokkuldormu"] = { 2, "", "Dokkuldormu was among the dragons taken hostage by the djaradin in Harrowsdeep as part of Iridikron's gambit to prevent Neltharion and the Aspects from collapsing the subterranean labyrinth." },
  ["domeel"] = { 2, "husband of the elderly innkeeper of Bradensbrook", "Domeel is the husband of the elderly innkeeper of Bradensbrook, Eliyah. 
According to Eliyah, they spent many years wandering until Domeel decided he wanted to settle." },
  ["doofus"] = { 2, "member Creedy's gang of bounty hunters", "Doofus was a member Creedy's gang of bounty hunters. He was killed by Hemet Nesingwary when the bounty hunters where hunting three frostsaber cubs, that Hemet was protecting." },
  ["dorthar"] = { 2, "centaur", "Dorthar is a centaur who, after being abandoned by his kind after the Cataclysm, helped the Garad'kra defeat Aratas and his centaur army. Dorthar went on to join the Horde himself, the first of his race to do so." },
  ["dorus"] = { 2, "Lordaeronian noble", "Dorus was a Lordaeronian noble and the father of Turalyon. He and his wife died when Turalyon was an infant, leaving Turalyon to be raised by the Church of the Holy Light." },
  ["dougan"] = { 2, "human paladin", "Dougan is a human paladin who fought with Kardan and Voldana during the Second War in battling the Horde. In the aftermath of the war, he settled near Grand Hamlet with his wife Adena and his twin baby girls: Loania and Lieren." },
  ["dracos"] = { 2, "individual", "Dracos is an individual who sponsored the Queen Mae during the Speedbarge Boat Race." },
  ["dralad"] = { 2, "adventurous orange proto-dragon", "Dralad was an adventurous orange proto-dragon. He was the brother of Alexstrasza and Ysera, and the three of them were the only survivors of their clutch." },
  ["dras"] = { 2, "orc assassin", "Dras was an orc assassin who helped escort carts loaded with supplies of water for the Horde in Mulgore shortly after the Cataclysm. He was slain by a group of quilboar along with Izwix and Grotz." },
  ["dreamwalker"] = { 2, "mount wolf", "The great black wolf Dreamwalker was the mount wolf and companion of Mother Kashur. Though Kashur used Dreamwalker as a mount and she was old and decrepit, she vowed to keep walking to Oshu'gun for as long as she could walk." },
  ["dresaelus"] = { 2, "kyrian commemorated in the Ancient Memorial in Bastion wh...", "Dresaelus is a kyrian commemorated in the Ancient Memorial in Bastion which blesses anyone who touches it. He invented single use glider." },
  ["dresh-khevan"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of Dresh-Khevan, who was once known as Khevan al Retaresh, is found within the southwestern courtyard of the Court of the Harvesters in Revendreth." },
  ["dubra'jin (god)"] = { 2, "", "Dubra'jin is one of the forgotten gods of Zul'Drak. The Zandalari in Zul'Drak have an outpost near his statue, having established an outpost of the same name providing them with protection from the Drakkari in exchange for many Gundrak Raptor Eggs." },
  ["duke reginald baradin ii"] = { 2, "founder", "Duke Reginald Baradin II was the founder and leader of Baradin's Wardens. After his death, he was succeeded by Commander Marcus Johnson." },
  ["duligosa"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Duligosa was a blue dragon who was killed by Neltharion's betrayal during the War of the Ancients. Her name is on a Faded Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["duree"] = { 2, "old human widow", "Duree was an old human widow and a secretary working for Jaina Proudmoore. She was known to wear spectacles and to frustrate her master by questioning her decisions." },
  ["duun"] = { 2, "orc warrior", "Duun was an orc warrior who fought alongside Broxigar to hold a mountain pass against the Burning Legion during the Battle of Mount Hyjal. He was beheaded by a demon, his head bouncing along the ground several seconds before his torso collapsed." },
  ["dwendel"] = { 2, "young redheaded gnome", "Dwendel is a young redheaded gnome who came with Gelbin Mekkatorque to the meeting in Darnassus. He is said to have a new possible weapon that may be able to fire fifty arrows in a minute." },
  ["e'ira"] = { 2, "naaru", "E'ira is a naaru that helped build the Exodar and designed the Crystal Hall as a calm and quiet place. There is also a mural of E'ira in the hall." },
  ["eadrik"] = { 2, "worgen", "Eadrik was a worgen that served as Genn Greymane's messenger and loyal aide. He did various tasks for Genn, such as spying on the Highborne, whom Genn didn't seem to trust due to their reputation." },
  ["earth mother"] = { 2, "gentle", "The Earth Mother, also known as the Earthmother or Mother Earth, is a gentle, seemingly transcendent and immortal being worshiped primarily by tauren (although also acknowledged by some orc shaman, the centaur, and at least one frost nymph) as the..." },
  ["edgar balloo"] = { 2, "son of Sully", "Edgar Balloo is the son of Sully and Sara Balloo." },
  ["edward the odd"] = { 2, "very eccentric human paladin", "Edward the Odd is a very eccentric human paladin. His nickname \"the Odd\" probably stems from his abnormal sense of fashion." },
  ["egalin"] = { 2, "first summoner of a voidwalker into Azeroth", "Egalin was the first summoner of a voidwalker into Azeroth. He detailed the process in his grimoire." },
  ["egnion"] = { 2, "leader of the black dragonflight's Shadowscales", "Egnion was the leader of the black dragonflight's Shadowscales. He spent most of his time afield spying on the Primalist forces." },
  ["egrigos"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Egrigos was a blue dragon who was killed in a magical accident. His name is on a Fresh Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["eidre"] = { 2, "human mage student of Dalaran", "Eidre was a human mage student of Dalaran and former fiancée of Alodi, who lived more than 2,600 years ago before the First War. Her parents owned some land by Brightwater Lake." },
  ["eimear"] = { 2, "Queen of Ironforge", "Eimear was the Queen of Ironforge, wife of King Magni Bronzebeard and mother of Princess Moira. After Moira's birth, Magni worried that something would take their daughter away from them." },
  ["eitrigg (alternate universe)"] = { 2, "orc", "Eitrigg was an orc who dwelt on the planet of Draenor as a member of the Blackrock clan and follower of Blackhand. During his lifetime, he met with Grommash Hellscream and was considered by him an honorable orc." },
  ["elanu"] = { 2, "female night elf killed by Ralaar", "Elanu was a female night elf killed by Ralaar and Arvell while they had lost their minds to the Pack Form." },
  ["elarisiel"] = { 2, "night elf", "Elarisiel was a night elf who sought out Illidan Stormrage in Outland to fight the Burning Legion, becoming one of the first Illidari demon hunters he trained. She was wounded during the invasion of Nathreza, but was saved by Illidan and Vandel an..." },
  ["eli blackfinger"] = { 2, "son of the famous blacksmith Nori Blackfinger", "Eli Blackfinger was the son of the famous blacksmith Nori Blackfinger. His mother died during his birth." },
  ["elinor"] = { 2, "Forsaken priestess serving the Conclave in the Netherligh...", "Elinor is a Forsaken priestess serving the Conclave in the Netherlight Temple. One night, after Calia Menethil had spoken with Saa'ra and was heading back to her room, Elinor approached her and excitedly informed her of King Anduin's plans for a G..." },
  ["elistrasza"] = { 2, "", "Elistrasza was among the dragons taken hostage by the djaradin in Harrowsdeep as part of Iridikron's gambit to prevent Neltharion and the Aspects from collapsing the subterranean labyrinth. Lailastrasza recognized her from her work in the Ruby Lif..." },
  ["eliyah"] = { 2, "elderly innkeeper of the inn in Bradensbrook", "Eliyah is the elderly innkeeper of the inn in Bradensbrook. He greeted and introduced himself to Lor'themar Theron and Thalyssra when they stopped to visit the inn there." },
  ["ellaene"] = { 2, "night elf Sentinel", "Ellaene was a night elf Sentinel, the wife of Elyrion Fogsong, and the mother of Arietta. According to Elyrion, she was \"Funny and quick and sweeter than honey to those she loved\"." },
  ["ellaria"] = { 2, "", "Ellaria was one of the high elves of Quel'lithien Lodge who succumbed to the corruption of a magical item found by Ranger-Lord Hawkspear, which transformed them into Wretched. Kirkian Dawnshield, who managed to avoid being corrupted by fleeing fro..." },
  ["ellegos"] = { 2, "member of the blue dragonflight", "Ellegos was a member of the blue dragonflight who defected to the Primalist cause. Ellegos was among those taken to the dungeons of the Obsidian Citadel for questioning." },
  ["ellegosa"] = { 2, "member of the blue dragonflight", "Ellegosa was a member of the blue dragonflight who defected to the Primalist cause. Ellegosa intended to open a passageway between the Chittering Caverns and Algeth'ar Academy for the Primalists to launch an assault on Malygos' forces through." },
  ["elmarine"] = { 2, "high elf mage", "Elmarine is a high elf mage.
At some point after the Cataclysm, she visited Flayers' Point in Desolace where she was noticed by Aramar Thorne." },
  ["elonia"] = { 2, "", "Elonia is one of the main characters of  [A Steamy Romance Novel: Nightborne of the Living Dead]." },
  ["elune"] = { 2, "moon goddess of the cosmic realm of Life", "Elune is a moon goddess of the cosmic realm of Life. Her sister and counterpart is the Winter Queen, one of the Eternal Ones of Death." },
  ["elyrion fogsong"] = { 2, "elderly", "Elyrion Fogsong is an elderly and very skilled night elf alchemist. After suffering a great personal loss, he chose to live alone in a bog on the slopes of Mount Hyjal, but this ultimately changed as the result of his friendship with the Sentinel ..." },
  ["emigos"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Emigos was a blue dragon who was killed by Neltharion's betrayal during the War of the Ancients. His name is on a Faded Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["emily (scourge invasion)"] = { 2, "human from Lordaeron", "Emily was a human from Lordaeron who was supposed to have received a final letter from her lover." },
  ["emperor dojan ii"] = { 2, "emperor of the mogu", "Emperor Dojan II was an emperor of the mogu. Even by mogu standards, the reign of Emperor Dojan II was short and brutish." },
  ["endemion"] = { 2, "", "Endemion was responsible for guarding Ikronia's prison alongside Sandesia the night that Raszageth and her forces attacked the Reach. He was sent away from his post by Ignion to join the battle." },
  ["enderman"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Enderman was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["erbag"] = { 2, "member of the Order of Tirisfal", "Erbag, who lived some eight centuries ago, was a member of the Order of Tirisfal.
Erbag supported the council's decision to make Aegwynn the new Guardian." },
  ["erik (human)"] = { 2, "innkeeper/bartender of Demonsbane Inn", "Erik is the innkeeper/bartender of Demonsbane Inn and Tavern located on Theramore Isle. His brother was Olaf." },
  ["erik fallrook"] = { 2, "arrogant son of Terrence Fallrook", "Erik Fallrook was an arrogant son of Terrence Fallrook who lived in the Fallrook Estate. His family owned a winery." },
  ["erthalif"] = { 2, "high elf mage", "Erthalif was a high elf mage that died three hundred years before the Third War. Aegwynn was given access to his redoubt after his death." },
  ["ery"] = { 2, "Kul Tiran tidesage", "Ery was a Kul Tiran tidesage and one of the two main characters in the Kul Tiran folktale \"Why the Mermaids Left Boralus\", which tells of the love between her and the mermaid Halia." },
  ["esme"] = { 2, "unknown race", "Esme is an unknown race who is acquainted with Auntie Stormstout. She was mentioned by her when she accidentally mistook Chen for Zan." },
  ["estes"] = { 2, "", "Estes is one of the survivors of the battle of Shattrath City. He was affected by the red mist, and in the months following his escape, started the change into a Broken." },
  ["ethylar"] = { 2, "high elf mage at Nallorath's father court", "Ethylar was a high elf mage at Nallorath's father court and a member of the Council of Tirisfal 2,600 years before the First War. She battled against Kathra'natir who stole the Amulet of Waters." },
  ["etries"] = { 2, "member of the Council of Oracles associated with the Arch...", "Etries was a member of the Council of Oracles associated with the Architects, one of the four aspects of K'areshi society. She also held membership among the Ravel." },
  ["faedra ambershade"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of Faedra Ambershade is found in Revendreth in the upper level of the Catacombs of Regret, to the right of the entrance of the tower located there, belonging to a night elf who died during the War of the Shifting Sands." },
  ["fala fizzlesprocket"] = { 2, "character in the story A Very Smokywood Winter Veil told ...", "Fala Fizzlesprocket is a character in the story A Very Smokywood Winter Veil told by Wulmort Jinglepocket during the Smokywood Storytime. She has a robot pet called Bolts." },
  ["faldir"] = { 2, "human of Strom", "Faldir was a human of Strom and one of the last members of Thoradin's line to dwell in Arathor, circa 1,200 BDP. Following the gradual fracturing of Arathor into independent kingdoms and the departure of Strom's noble families from the capital, Fa..." },
  ["falric (cycle of hatred)"] = { 2, "", "Falric was amongst the five mage students of Magna Scavell. As the others, he also was against Aegwynn becoming the next Guardian." },
  ["faltora"] = { 2, "younger brother of Koltira Deathweaver", "Faltora was the younger brother of Koltira Deathweaver. He wanted to ask Merriel to attend a banquet with him, but was a little shy." },
  ["falwulf"] = { 2, "", "Falwulf was one of the dwarves under Rom's command. He accompanied him on a mission to Grim Batol." },
  ["fang'gar"] = { 2, "companion of Jaruk Bloodfyre", "Fang'gar was the companion of Jaruk Bloodfyre. When Jaruk and Leena escaped to Zangarmarsh, Fang'gar found them and remained with them." },
  ["fanghorn"] = { 2, "tauren member of the Twilight's Hammer", "Fanghorn was a tauren member of the Twilight's Hammer. He was a part of the group assisting Garona Halforcen in ruining the peace treaty between the Horde and the Alliance." },
  ["fara boltbreaker"] = { 2, "primary reporter for the Gadgetzan Times", "Fara Boltbreaker is a primary reporter for the Gadgetzan Times, having had stories featured in the first two issues. Little is known about her personal life or even what she looks like." },
  ["farand"] = { 2, "Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War", "Farand was a Wildhammer dwarf during the Second War. He and his thane, Kurdran Wildhammer, were the first to notice the orcs in the Hinterlands after their retreat from Hillsbrad." },
  ["farkigos"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Farkigos was a blue dragon who was killed in a magical accident. His name is on a Fresh Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["farrol"] = { 2, "human rider", "Farrol was a human rider who Danath Trollbane chose to take with him along with half of the military in Stormwind City to the Dark Portal. He was very young for he never participated in the Second War or fought an orc in his life." },
  ["featherbeard"] = { 2, "honored Wildhammer dwarf", "Featherbeard was an honored Wildhammer dwarf who was a gryphon breeder and trainer. He lived in Featherbeard's Hovel." },
  ["felgrim"] = { 2, "Forsaken warlock", "Felgrim is a Forsaken warlock and member of the Garad'kra." },
  ["felyae"] = { 2, "dwarf", "Felyae is a dwarf who took Li Li and Chen Stormstouts on her wagon and carried them through Tanaris. She compared the tol'vir to centaurs as they are just big cats instead of horses." },
  ["fen"] = { 2, "pandaren", "Fen is a pandaren that is either a friend or relative to Lorewalker Shuchun." },
  ["fenistrasza"] = { 2, "red dragon", "Fenistrasza was a red dragon who died fighting the djaradin named Tarjin the Blind by holding her in a volcano for three days straight. Her skull would later be taken by the adventurers and given to the Dragonscale Expedition." },
  ["fently"] = { 2, "human", "Fently is a human who traveled with the Ashvane Trading Company expedition on the Maiden's Whisper to the Siren Isle. He was described as a brute." },
  ["feral scar (traveler)"] = { 2, "yeti", "Feral Scar is a yeti." },
  ["ferelyn bloodscorn"] = { 2, "blood elf member of the Argent Dawn", "Ferelyn Bloodscorn was a blood elf member of the Argent Dawn. He was the first to accept Darion Mograine's call for help in storming Naxxramas to rescue his father, Alexandros Mograine." },
  ["fergun"] = { 2, "Wildhammer dwarf gryphon rider", "Fergun is a Wildhammer dwarf gryphon rider. He was stationed at Allerian Stronghold, looking after Kurdran Wildhammer's gryphon after his presumed death." },
  ["fezhar"] = { 2, "orc warrior", "Fezhar was an orc warrior who fought alongside Broxigar to hold a mountain pass against the Burning Legion during the Battle of Mount Hyjal. His body was dissolved when a demon belched fel fire on him." },
  ["filigosa"] = { 2, "blue dragon", "Filigosa was a blue dragon who died from an unknown disease. Her name is on a Faded Gravestone at the Veiled Ossuary." },
  ["filora"] = { 2, "green drake", "Filora is a green drake and one of Lailastrasza's companions who fought alongside her against the djaradin." },
  ["fire golem"] = { 2, "creature created through the power of the Demon Soul", "A fire golem (aka golem of fire) was a creature created through the power of the Demon Soul. It was a humanoid figure with a flaming bone shape and burning skull for a head." },
  ["first forgelite"] = { 2, "kyrian", "The First Forgelite was a kyrian who served as the first Forgelite Prime of Bastion. She wielded the hammer Phaestus, Genesis of Aeons, and was responsible for the creation of the first centurions and the Spires of Ascension, as well as the design..." },
  ["flint broadshot"] = { 2, "human hunter", "Flint Broadshot was a human hunter. One day he entered the Blue Recluse in Stormwind, seeking to buy ale for him and his friend." },
  ["fontane"] = { 2, "human of the Stromgarde Militia", "Fontane was a human of the Stromgarde Militia who fought against the Syndicate in Arathi Highlands. He fell and his badge was taken by his killer, kept as a trophy until its retrieval by hired adventurers." },
  ["foror"] = { 2, "person referenced in World of Warcraft by various items", "Foror was a person referenced in World of Warcraft by various items and characters." },
  ["forx"] = { 2, "seaman aboard the Horde trading ship Orath'ar serving und...", "Forx is the seaman aboard the Horde trading ship Orath'ar serving under Captain Bolik. During the attack by pirates, Forx repelled the attack and was rewarded by the captain with his full despite the lost cargo." },
  ["four-fingered fong"] = { 2, "pandaren", "Four-Fingered Fong is a pandaren who can sell items on the Black Market Auction House." },
  ["frandis farley"] = { 2, "Forsaken warrior", "Captain Frandis Farley was a Forsaken warrior, who in life lived in the human kingdom of Stormwind. It has been observed that when not speaking, Frandis's jaw drops into a permanent gaping expression." },
  ["friar burlingham"] = { 2, "member of the Argent Crusade", "Friar Burlingham is a member of the Argent Crusade. He came to Outfitter Mendelev to stock up swimwear for his trip to Hardwrench Hideaway." },
  ["fritz fizzlesprocket"] = { 2, "character in the story A Very Smokywood Winter Veil told ...", "Frits Fizzlesprocket is a character in the story A Very Smokywood Winter Veil told by Wulmort Jinglepocket during the Smokywood Storytime.
Professor Frits has gone missing, and his daughter's only wish is for him to come back." },
  ["garth beeks"] = { 2, "undead", "Garth Beeks is an undead who wrote to the Gadgetzan Times, asking them to contact Gerald Crowe and ask him if he could introduce him to his wife." },
  ["general dugall"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of General Dugall is found in Revendreth in the Archivam, in the area behind the manor." },
  ["generous dan"] = { 2, "", "Generous Dan was not captain of the Dread Crew for long, but is still regarded as the best captain ever." },
  ["gerald crowe"] = { 2, "human", "Gerald Crowe is a human that used to live in Stratholme with his wife, Lavinia, prior to the Third War. When the Scourge came the two of them were separated and Lavinia killed." },
  ["giles flintridge"] = { 2, "younger brother of Tilloa Flintridge", "Giles Flintridge was the younger brother of Tilloa Flintridge, the son of a human noble of Stormwind, and a student to Stalvan Mistmantle. He was murdered the same night that Stalvan took his revenge." },
  ["gnopetto bizzfuse"] = { 2, "gnome inventor", "Gnopetto Bizzfuse was a gnome inventor who created the Blingtron unit. He worked from his workshop in Tanaris until he died several years before the third invasion of the Burning Legion when the sea arose." },
  ["graun blump"] = { 2, "good fisherman", "Graun Blump is Gubber Blump's cousin. She is a good fisherman, though not as good as Gubber." },
  ["gregor fizzwuzz"] = { 2, "gnome", "Gregor Fizzwuzz is a gnome who was interviewed by the Gadgetzan Times, asking him about why he is helping the Brassbolts brothers building a race cart." },
  ["gregory adams"] = { 2, "human mage", "Gregory Adams is a human mage. He wrote a letter to Kirin Tor Monthly, about his friends constantly asking for food, drinks and portals." },
  ["greyhoof farwanderer"] = { 2, "apparent leader of the Farwanderers tauren tribe", "Greyhoof Farwanderer is the apparent leader of the Farwanderers tauren tribe, and an elderly tauren who had served Cairne Bloodhoof faithfully prior to his death. Though he is loyal to his son and successor, Baine, he has become disheartened with ..." },
  ["gunnar flyntrock"] = { 2, "leader of a group of Dark Iron dwarves", "Gunnar Flyntrock was the leader of a group of Dark Iron dwarves.
When Thargas Anvilmar, Varian \"Lo'Gosh\" Wrynn, Valeera Sanguinar and Broll Bearmantle were travelling through the Wetlands they were attacked by Gunmar and his dark iron dwarves." },
  ["halsvir fjinnsonn"] = { 2, "vrykul", "Halsvir Fjinnsonn is a vrykul who recorded a chapter in The Legend of Odyn." },
  ["harbinger elm"] = { 2, "agent from Lordaeron", "Harbinger Elm is an agent from Lordaeron, but unknown from what organization, that was to meet with the Grimtotem tribe. They were going to form a working relationship, so long as the Grimtotem were completely obedient to them." },
  ["heavy chan"] = { 2, "large pandaren from One Keg", "Heavy Chan is a large pandaren from One Keg and the son of a wealthy alchemist. He was one of the ten volunteers who decided to take The Trial of the Red Blossoms in order to join the Shado-pan." },
  ["high general abbendis"] = { 2, "father of High General Brigitte Abbendis", "High General Abbendis was one of the founders of the original Scarlet Crusade. He was the father of High General Brigitte Abbendis, and once, a paladin and general of the Order of the Silver Hand." },
  ["high priestess navi derolan"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of High Priestess Navi DeRolan is found in the Dredgewood in Revendreth." },
  ["hildy bufferpolish"] = { 2, "individual", "Hildy Bufferpolish is an individual who engineered the Queen Mae during the Speedbarge Boat Race." },
  ["hjalmar anvilmar"] = { 2, "brother of Thargas Anvilmar", "Hjalmar Anvilmar, nicknamed Hjal, was the brother of Thargas Anvilmar. He trained Varian Wrynn and taught him the \"Anvilmar feint\", a dwarf combat stance." },
  ["j'amogg bloodfyre"] = { 2, "father of Jaruk", "J'amogg Bloodfyre is the father of Jaruk and J'argg Bloodfyre." },
  ["j'argg bloodfyre"] = { 2, "Shadowmoon orc", "J'argg Bloodfyre was a Shadowmoon orc who lived on Draenor at the start of the genocide of the draenei. He became a leader of raids on the remaining draenei, and often urged his brother, Jaruk Bloodfyre, to drink the Blood of Mannoroth as well and..." },
  ["jacob felstone"] = { 2, "son of Emma Felstone", "Jacob \"Jake\" Felstone was a son of Emma Felstone and Jem, and the brother of James and John. All three were warriors of Lordaeron, acting as royal guards to King Terenas Menethil." },
  ["james ashvane"] = { 2, "leader of House Ashvane", "Lord James Ashvane was the leader of House Ashvane. He served as a captain in the Kul Tiran fleets, where he died during the invasion of Durotar alongside Daelin Proudmoore." },
  ["james blackridge"] = { 2, "son of a farming family", "James Blackridge, called Jimmy in his youth, is the son of a farming family, who live and work a farm outside Goldshire. Jimmy had a problem with responsibility as he was not able to do his chores." },
  ["james felstone"] = { 2, "son of Emma Felstone", "James \"Jem\" Felstone was a son of Emma Felstone and Jem. Bearing his father's name, he was the oldest of three brothers." },
  ["jarim balnir"] = { 2, "son of the horsebreeder Jorum Balnir", "Jarim Balnir was the son of the horsebreeder Jorum Balnir and his wife Vara, and a childhood friend of Prince Arthas Menethil. He was the same age as Arthas." },
  ["jaruk bloodfyre"] = { 2, "Shadowmoon orc shaman", "Jaruk Bloodfyre was a Shadowmoon orc shaman who lived on Draenor at the start of the genocide of the draenei. Having felt the elements abandoning him, he was wary of the course of his people and refused to drink the Blood of Mannoroth from the Cha..." },
  ["jerias bloodvein"] = { 2, "undead captain of the Garrote", "Jerias Bloodvein is the undead captain of the Garrote. He is a member of the Bloodsail Buccaneers." },
  ["joe barker"] = { 2, "worgen from Gilneas", "Joe Barker, nicknamed Silent Joe, was a worgen from Gilneas and the third mate of the Wavestrider.
He was originally a pirate member of the Brashtide Crew and later of the Blackwater Raiders." },
  ["john felstone"] = { 2, "son of Emma Felstone", "John \"Jack\" Felstone was a son of Emma Felstone and Jem, and the brother of James and Jacob. All three were warriors of Lordaeron, acting as royal guards to King Terenas Menethil." },
  ["jolta candleflash"] = { 2, "goblin", "Jolta Candleflash is a goblin who works for the Gadgetzan Times." },
  ["jonas cobb"] = { 2, "cook of the Wavestrider", "Jonas Cobb, nicknamed Old Cobb, was the cook of the Wavestrider. He had an assistant, 10 year-old-boy named Keelhaul Watt‎." },
  ["jorum balnir"] = { 2, "head of the Balnir family of horse-breeders", "Jorum Balnir was the head of the Balnir family of horse-breeders, the husband of Vara, and father of Jarim.
In his youth, Prince Arthas Menethil often sneaked off to the Balnir Farmstead to admire Jorum's horses and play with Jarim." },
  ["karandra fordring"] = { 2, "wife of Lord Paladin Tirion Fordring of Hearthglen", "Lady Karandra Fordring was the wife of Lord Paladin Tirion Fordring of Hearthglen." },
  ["keda bloomblade"] = { 2, "night elf Sentinel", "Keda Bloomblade is a night elf Sentinel and the protagonist of the short story \"Stones, Moss, and Tears\"." },
  ["kedehern falamar"] = { 2, "son of Brogan", "Kedehern Falamar was the son of Brogan and brother of Aodhan. He chose to become a paladin of the Silver Hand, something his father approved of, ten years before the start of the Nexus War." },
  ["kelantir bloodblade"] = { 2, "blood elf Blood Knight", "Kelantir Bloodblade was a blood elf Blood Knight. She trained with Lady Liadrin and served directly under the military leader of Quel'Thalas, Ranger-General Halduron Brightwing." },
  ["kettara bloodthirst"] = { 2, "orc shaman of the Earthen Ring", "Kettara Bloodthirst was an orc shaman of the Earthen Ring." },
  ["kilrogg deadeye"] = { 2, "chieftain of the Bleeding Hollow clan", "Kilrogg Deadeye was the chieftain of the Bleeding Hollow clan. He is so named because he lost his left eye." },
  ["klarissa cartwright"] = { 2, "human", "Klarissa Cartwright is a human who wrote to Fizzle Goblinseer, as she was concerned about her husband spending more time with a succubus named Aelneth than her." },
  ["klaxz boompowder"] = { 2, "former trade prince of the Steamwheedle Cartel", "Klaxz Boompowder is a former trade prince of the Steamwheedle Cartel who became the first known victim of the Uninvited Guest." },
  ["kor'ak bloodspike"] = { 2, "presumably orcish witness to the Cataclysm in the Souther...", "Kor'ak Bloodspike was a presumably orcish witness to the Cataclysm in the Southern Barrens that was swallowed by the earth during the chaos." },
  ["kova broadhorn"] = { 2, "tauren shaman", "Kova Broadhorn is a tauren shaman and novice alchemist. It seems that she once anticipated in a battle at Red Rocks." },
  ["krank axeljink"] = { 2, "gnome from Tinker Town", "Krank Axeljink was a gnome from Tinker Town, chosen to be a gnomish representative to the New Council of Tirisfal. He invented a device that would draw power from the other council members into their chosen representative (which would, of course, ..." },
  ["krazzel crashfuse"] = { 2, "diabolical level 62 goblin featured in the 100 or Bust! t...", "Krazzel Crashfuse is a diabolical level 62 goblin featured in the 100 or Bust! trailer." },
  ["krohm dawnhammer"] = { 2, "dwarf paladin", "Krohm Dawnhammer was a dwarf paladin who helped the citizens of Lordaeron during the Scourging of Lordaeron. He forged his own armor, which was bolstered by the Light." },
  ["lady delth"] = { 2, "member of the Kirin Tor", "Lady Delth was a member of the Kirin Tor who studied elven history. When Khadgar was sent to Medivh, she requested that he find out all he could about elven history from Medivh's library." },
  ["lady mara fordragon"] = { 2, "High Clerist of the Kingdom of Stormwind during the First...", "Lady Mara Fordragon was the High Clerist of the Kingdom of Stormwind during the First War. She became a patron of the Stormwindian refugees who fled to Lordaeron after the war." },
  ["lieutenant alverold"] = { 2, "", "Lieutenant Alverold was one of Daelin Proudmoore's lieutenants and made up a part of the fleet which sailed to Durotar in search of Jaina Proudmoore. While Proudmoore headed towards land, he ordered Alverold to take an exploratory fleet and scout ..." },
  ["lord agrovane"] = { 2, "human", "Lord Agrovane is a human who bought Rehgar Earthfury as a gladiator from guards at an Alliance internment camp. Eventually, however, Rehgar was able to escape." },
  ["lord ashbury the 1st"] = { 2, "Gilnean noble", "Lord Ashbury the 1st was a Gilnean noble and the father of Baron Ashbury. Lord Ashbury helped King Archibald Greymane build Gilneas up to a nation of great power." },
  ["lord blackforest"] = { 2, "night elf noble", "Lord Blackforest was a night elf noble. He was one of the many nobles who looked to Jarod Shadowsong for leadership during the later battles against the Burning Legion." },
  ["lord del'theon"] = { 2, "night elf noble", "Lord Del'theon was a night elf noble. He was one of many leaders killed during the fight against the Burning Legion." },
  ["lore character"] = { 2, "character mentioned in lore", "A lore character is a character mentioned in lore, but not present in any Warcraft or World of Warcraft games." },
  ["loreli fallglade"] = { 2, "night elf", "Loreli Fallglade is a night elf. It appears that she is a caretaker for the young, but is unable to have children herself." },
  ["maaklu cloudcaller"] = { 2, "tauren shaman", "Maaklu was a tauren shaman who accompanied Cairne and Garrosh through Garrosh's Landing. There they were attacked by Kvaldir." },
  ["madoran bronzebeard"] = { 2, "ruling thane of Ironforge", "Madoran Bronzebeard was the ruling thane of Ironforge and the Bronzebeard clan before and during the War of the Three Hammers. The Bronzebeard clan, ruled by Thane Madoran Bronzebeard, held close ties to the High King and stood as the traditional ..." },
  ["maim blackhand"] = { 2, "son of the former Warchief Blackhand the Destroyer", "Maim Blackhand was the son of the former Warchief Blackhand the Destroyer and the brother of Dal'rend and Griselda. Along with Dal'rend, Maim served as the co-leader of the Black Tooth Grin clan until his death in Blackrock Mountain." },
  ["makasa flintwill"] = { 2, "human girl", "Makasa Flintwill is a human girl who comes from Booty Bay, with her ancestors coming from Stromgarde. She is a capable hunter and tracker." },
  ["margulf blaggon"] = { 2, "dwarven miner", "Margulf Blaggon is a dwarven miner and author, who spent most his time digging for ore in the mountains of Khaz Modan a few decades before World of Warcraft. During his time there he wrote the book The Stresses of Iron, which players seeking to he..." },
  ["marjani flintwill"] = { 2, "human pirate captain of the Makemba of the Blackwater Rai...", "Marjani Flintwill is a human pirate captain of the Makemba of the Blackwater Raiders's fleet. She is very capable with various weapons." },
  ["marla fipps"] = { 2, "human buried at Deathknell in Tirisfal Glade", "Marla Fipps is a human buried at Deathknell in Tirisfal Glade. She would be killed by her undead husband but she loved him so much that she wanted him to be buried with her as her final wish." },
  ["mary brown"] = { 2, "human deckhand on the Wavestrider", "Mary Brown was a human deckhand on the Wavestrider. She assisted Captain Greydon Thorne in the attack against the Bloodsail Buccaneers on the Sea King, personally freeing the captured crew, along with Durgan One-God." },
  ["master feng"] = { 2, "battle", "Discipline is not a war that is won. It is a battle, constantly fought." },
  ["master j. capaldi"] = { 2, "deceased human buried at Barrowknoll Cemetery in Drustvar", "Master J. Capaldi is a deceased human buried at Barrowknoll Cemetery in Drustvar." },
  ["messenger fishtail"] = { 2, "grummle", "Messenger Fishtail is a grummle who was sent by Chen Stormstout to find his niece Li Li. He found her in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms and delivered her a letter." },
  ["miles corebender"] = { 2, "gnome warrior", "Miles Corebender is a gnome warrior who accompanied Kova Broadhorn on her quest for the reclusive orc seer Dhambeela. He accompanied Kova in the hopes that an epic song would be sung about him and his adventures." },
  ["mina fintallas"] = { 2, "wife of Parqual Fintallas", "Mina Fintallas is the wife of Parqual Fintallas and the mother of Philia. Before the Third War, the Fintallas family lived in their modest but comfortable chambers in Capital City." },
  ["miner fitzgerald"] = { 2, "miner of Hillsbrad Fields", "Miner Fitzgerald was a miner of Hillsbrad Fields. It is unknown what became of him after the Forsaken took over." },
  ["modimus anvilmar"] = { 2, "last High King of the united dwarves of Ironforge prior t...", "Modimus Anvilmar was the last High King of the united dwarves of Ironforge prior to the War of the Three Hammers. An immense statue of Modimus stands guard at the Gates of Ironforge." },
  ["morgala darksquall"] = { 2, "powerful naga siren", "Morgala Darksquall was a powerful naga siren.
When Onyxia separated Varian Wrynn into two, Morgala and her naga attacked Onyxia." },
  ["morka bruggu"] = { 2, "orc soldier of the Horde", "Morka Bruggu is an orc soldier of the Horde. She participated in the war against the Burning Legion and later served as a guard in Orgrimmar before being assigned as one of Varok Saurfang's personal guards during the War of the Thorns." },
  ["mose canton"] = { 2, "quartermaster on the Wavestrider", "Mose Canton was the quartermaster on the Wavestrider. He died defending the ship against the Hidden, killed by Reigol Valdread." },
  ["mr. blackridge"] = { 2, "human farmer", "Mr. Blackridge is a human farmer who lives just outside Goldshire." },
  ["mr. cooper"] = { 2, "barrel maker from Moonbrook", "Mr. Cooper was a barrel maker from Moonbrook." },
  ["mr. cooper's brother"] = { 2, "", "Mr. Cooper's brother inherited the family business from his older brother." },
  ["mrs. blackridge"] = { 2, "human", "Mrs. Blackridge is a human who lives just outside Goldshire." },
  ["nal fizzletongue"] = { 2, "", "The sinstone of Nal Fizzletongue is found at the southwestern end of the Chalice District in Revendreth." },
  ["nalmeena darkfollow"] = { 2, "night elf warden", "Nalmeena Darkfollow is a night elf warden. A tower in Val'sharah is probably named after her: Darkfollow's Spire." },
  ["netty bronzebeard"] = { 2, "great-aunt of the three Bronzebeard brothers", "Netty Bronzebeard is a great-aunt of the three Bronzebeard brothers, Magni, Muradin, and Brann. They noted that she has a temper when someone moves her knitting." },
  ["nipskee fizzwidget"] = { 2, "goblin", "Nipskee Fizzwidget is a goblin who works for the Gadgetzan Times. He interviewed Nuxt Sparklespring about the engineering required to blow stuff up, and Nuxt was more than happy to give a demonstration." },
  ["nori blackfinger"] = { 2, "", "Nori Blackfinger was once a Master Weaponsmith living in the Searing Gorge, specifically at Thorium Point. His blades were some of the finest in the world, and adventurers far and wide traveled to Thorium Point to have a weapon made by him." },
  ["ol' dunken"] = { 2, "individual of the Bloodsail Buccaneers sent by Fleet Mast...", "Ol' Dunken is an individual of the Bloodsail Buccaneers sent by Fleet Master Firallon to scout an area in the Cape of Stranglethorn and to wait for the signal to attack Booty Bay in year 25." },
  ["oreg earthfury"] = { 2, "tauren shaman with the Earthen Ring", "Oreg Earthfury was a tauren shaman with the Earthen Ring that lived sometime after the era of the War of the Three Hammers. When Sorcerer-thane Thaurissan released Ragnaros and shattered the Redridge Mountains of the Eastern Kingdoms, the effects ..." },
  ["p. diddimus"] = { 2, "gnome intern working for the highly esteemed Gnomeregan G...", "P. Diddimus is the gnome intern working for the highly esteemed Gnomeregan Gnews Gnetwork. Diddimus was with Wendy Breezy interviewing Barley McFrothbeard, when asked to hold Barley's ale so that he could show off the flying mount, unfortunately D..." },
  ["penny flay"] = { 2, "daughter of Robby Flay", "Penny Flay is the daughter of Robby Flay. She has a taste for pumpkin pancakes and her father does his best to provide them for her." },
  ["private denning"] = { 2, "soldier of Honor Hold", "Private Denning was a soldier of Honor Hold who got killed by the Bleeding Hollow clan, his insignia now serving as a cursed talisman for them." },
  ["queen anub'izek"] = { 2, "founder of Azj-Kahet", "Queen Anub'izek was the founder of Azj-Kahet, and the first queen of the \"true nerubians\". According to the histories of Azj-Kahet, Anub'izek was a unique creature with the power of a lord and the memory of a sage, created by the \"dark ones\" to co..." },
  ["ragnok bloodreaver"] = { 2, "", "Ragnok Bloodreaver was one of the original death knights of the Horde, created by Gul'dan from the corpses of Stormwind knights and the spirits of the slain Shadow Council." },
  ["ralaar fangfire"] = { 2, "first worgen", "Ralaar Fangfire, also known as Alpha Prime, was the first worgen. A talented night elf druid who was able to surpass others in practicing the art of the pack form, he founded a group known as the Druids of the Pack and became their leader." },
  ["reynah firecaster"] = { 2, "blood elf mage", "Reynah Firecaster was a blood elf mage who, with Barnabas Grell attempted to avenge their loved ones who were killed by the Scarlet Crusade." },
  ["rinn firecaster"] = { 2, "blood elven apprentice jewelcrafter", "Rinn Firecaster was a blood elven apprentice jewelcrafter who specialized in dawnstones. He worked at Gallaran's in Silvermoon City." },
  ["ryton blackholme"] = { 2, "", "Ryton Blackholme was Hallowfall's finest blacksmith. He trained Raen Dawncavalyr and Lars Bronsmaelt from back when they were but \"cubs\"." },
  ["samuel coulter"] = { 2, "deceased human buried at Barrowknoll Cemetery in Drustvar", "Samuel Coulter is a deceased human buried at Barrowknoll Cemetery in Drustvar." },
  ["sarias colton"] = { 2, "human soldier of Stormwind", "Sarias Colton was a human soldier of Stormwind who had been killed and raised by the Scourge during the Third War. He later regained his sanity and joined the Forsaken." },
  ["seeker anewa"] = { 2, "ankoan of the Waveblade clan", "Seeker Anewa was an ankoan of the Waveblade clan who \"sought answers to questions not yet asked\" and \"slew the unknown with the blade of wisdom\". They lie buried at an Ankoan Burial Shrine in the Ashen Strand of Nazjatar." },
  ["serena everwind"] = { 2, "night elf priestess", "Serena Everwind was a night elf priestess who fought for the Kaldorei Resistance during the War of the Ancients. During one battle, she witnessed Dath'Remar Sunstrider wielding Felo'melorn against the Burning Legion, and the description of the bat..." },
  ["sergeant copperbolt"] = { 2, "gnome sergeant under the command of High Tinker Gelbin Me...", "Sergeant Copperbolt is a gnome sergeant under the command of High Tinker Gelbin Mekkatorque. He was a part of a group that had been sent to reconnoiter Sector 17 in Gnomeregan, the location of the High Tinker's quarters." },
  ["shadow priest anund"] = { 2, "dwarf priest", "Shadow Priest Anund was a dwarf priest who participated in the battle with the dread wyrm, Kaldrigos. He died due to standing in the dragon's arcane breath." },
  ["shu blindeye"] = { 2, "pandaren emperor of the Pandaren Empire", "Shu Blindeye was a pandaren emperor of the Pandaren Empire. The  [Pearl of Yu'lon] was carved during his reign in honor of the Jade Serpent." },
  ["slixi boompowder"] = { 2, "goblin", "Slixi Boompowder is a goblin who invented tossaways, a means of protection from the Uninvited Guest, after her husband, the Steamwheedle trade prince Klaxz Boompowder, fell victim to the creature. She has green eyes and her hair is arranged in rat..." },
  ["stasia fallshadow"] = { 2, "Forsaken mage", "Stasia Fallshadow is a Forsaken mage who had a special talent for translating ancient tomes. Around the time of Onyxia's death, she arrived to the Pools of Vision, where she used a scroll that she had received from an orc shaman a few months befor..." },
  ["strider ahu"] = { 2, "ankoan of the Waveblade clan \"who braved the currents of ...", "Strider Ahu was an ankoan of the Waveblade clan \"who braved the currents of distant depths.\" They lie buried at an Ankoan Burial Shrine in Thoras'tal Spire in Nazjatar." },
  ["tari cogg"] = { 2, "gnome mage of the Kirin Tor", "Tari Cogg was a gnome mage of the Kirin Tor. She was known as one of the foremost gnome magi in Dalaran." },
  ["taruka beastkiller"] = { 2, "young tuskarr fisher", "Taruka, later called Taruka Beastkiller, is a young tuskarr fisher and the titular protagonist of the short story \"One Small Tuskarr\"." },
  ["telkar doomhammer"] = { 2, "father of Warchief Orgrim Doomhammer", "Telkar Doomhammer was the father of Warchief Orgrim Doomhammer, and one of the best warriors in the Blackrock clan. He wielded the mighty Doomhammer, considered by some to be a weapon of prophecy." },
  ["terrence fallrook"] = { 2, "father of Cedrick", "Terrence Fallrook is the father of Cedrick and Erik and an owner of Fallrook Estate and its winery. He is described as a good and important man in Southshore and might have been a part in a tribunal of Erik's murder." },
  ["tharken bloodspike"] = { 2, "presumably orcish witness to the Cataclysm in the Souther...", "Tharken Bloodspike was a presumably orcish witness to the Cataclysm in the Southern Barrens that lost his brother during the chaos." },
  ["the bonebreaker"] = { 2, "nickname given to a female assassin", "The Bonebreaker was the nickname given to a female assassin who, after one of her victims came back from the dead, developed a habit of breaking their legs after killing them." },
  ["the caretaker"] = { 2, "venthyr", "The Caretaker was a venthyr and the former Harvester of Envy. The predecessor to the Tithelord, they were the 274th Caretaker." },
  ["the deathbringer (statue)"] = { 2, "nerubian depicted by a statue in the Skeins in the City o...", "The Deathbringer is a nerubian depicted by a statue in the Skeins in the City of Threads, on the southwestern side of the Royal Preservatorium. The statue's plaque can only be understood while under the effects of  [Potion of Polymorphic Translati..." },
  ["thunker axeljink"] = { 2, "member of the Council of Tirisfal", "Thunker Axeljink was a member of the Council of Tirisfal and the father of Krank Axeljink. He died while defending Gnomeregan against the invading troggs." },
  ["tihku fogcaller"] = { 2, "tauren drum maker in Bloodhoof Village in Mulgore", "Tihku Fogcaller is a tauren drum maker in Bloodhoof Village in Mulgore. Zekhan used to watch and enjoy his drummaking, especially the way he worked the sinew threads to pull the tanned heads taut over their frames." },
  ["tilloa flintridge"] = { 2, "daughter of a human noble of Stormwind", "Tilloa Flintridge was the daughter of a human noble of Stormwind." },
  ["toreth bluestar"] = { 2, "night elf \"Lorekeeper\"", "Toreth Bluestar is a night elf \"Lorekeeper\", meaning it is his duty to record the names and noteworthy deeds of his fellow kaldorei. He is small but handsome, with teal skin and a tangle of green hair." },
  ["twilight lord d'sak"] = { 2, "lord of the Twilight's Hammer", "Twilight Lord D'Sak is a lord of the Twilight's Hammer, and author of one of the True Believer articles sent to the cult's members in Silithus. He dictated that to ensure security of the texts, they should be distributed with an escort of armed cu..." },
  ["typoe crunchmode"] = { 2, "goblin", "Typoe Crunchmode is a goblin who works for the Gadgetzan Times as Editor-in-chief." },
  ["urheld darkstone"] = { 2, "", "Urheld Darkstone, despite being an alchemist of great skill, was thought insane by his contemporaries and, hence, did not share his research. Instead, he etched it onto tablets." },
  ["urluk cloud-killer"] = { 2, "warlock of the Stormreaver clan", "Urluk Cloud-killer is a warlock of the Stormreaver clan who followed Gul'dan into the Tomb of Sargeras. He was frightened by the guardians of the tomb, and so Gul'dan slapped him across the face." },
  ["vara balnir"] = { 2, "wife of Jorum Balnir", "Vara Balnir was the wife of Jorum Balnir and mother of Jarim. Her pride and joy was the snapdragon flowers that grew on the Balnir Farmstead." },
  ["vellcinda benton"] = { 2, "wife of Wyll Benton", "Vellcinda \"Elsie\" Benton was the wife of Wyll Benton and former Prime Governor of the Desolate Council which she founded to take care of the city in Sylvanas' absence. She was once a servant in a kitchen." },
  ["watersmith aiga"] = { 2, "ankoan of the Waveblade clan \"whose weapons always struck...", "Watersmith Aiga was an ankoan of the Waveblade clan \"whose weapons always struck true and carry on her legacy with every strike.\" She lies buried at an Ankoan Burial Shrine in Gorgonian Overlook in Nazjatar." },
  ["wendy breezy"] = { 2, "gnome reporter of the highly esteemed Gnomeregan Gnews Gn...", "Wendy Breezy is the gnome reporter of the highly esteemed Gnomeregan Gnews Gnetwork." },
  ["wuul breezerider"] = { 2, "tauren", "Wuul Breezerider is a tauren who comes from Mulgore. His wife died approximately 10 years before the Cataclysm." },
  ["wyll benton"] = { 2, "elderly servant of", "Wyll Benton was an elderly servant of Anduin Wrynn. He had been taking care of Anduin since the king was little and refusing his service would offend him." },
  ["yana bloodspear"] = { 2, "", "Yana Bloodspear has a large statue erected in her honor in the the Hall of Champions, located in the Scarlet Monastery in the Tirisfal Glades. She was born in Dalaran." },
  ["yao firmpaw"] = { 2, "pandaren physician", "Yao Firmpaw was a pandaren physician whose career was so spectacular, his name is still associated with health and wellness in the Valley of the Four Winds. He never married; his heart was forever broken when his love, a young lorewalker named Lin..." },
  ["yu fei"] = { 2, "pandaren mage", "Yu Fei is a pandaren mage who was opening portals for everyone who needed them during the trial of Garrosh Hellscream. She was also magically unlocking and locking Garrosh's cell when necessary." },
  ["zhahara darksquall"] = { 2, "naga assigned by her superiors to find the lost continent...", "Zhahara Darksquall was a naga assigned by her superiors to find the lost continent of Pandaria. However, Zhahara herself was obsessed with finding the Wandering Isle and the Pearl of Pandaria." },
  ["zur'ak firefist"] = { 2, "troll shaman of the Earthen Ring", "Zur'ak Firefist is a troll shaman of the Earthen Ring and a member of its Elder Council. He believed that the elements had abandoned the Earthen Ring." },
}) do
  if not IABD.nameOverrides[name] then
    IABD.nameOverrides[name] = entry
  end
end